Our Mission

SOAR empowers student researchers to become the heroes of tomorrow's scientific breakthroughs. We provide a platform where undergraduate and graduate students can showcase their research, connect with peers, and develop the superpowers needed for academic excellence.

Why Should Students Attend SOAR?

Present Your Research

Showcase your work to peers and faculty

Network with Heroes

Connect with fellow student researchers

Win Awards

Compete for research excellence prizes

Learn from Experts

Attend workshops and keynote sessions

SOAR's History

Since 2015, SOAR has been the premier student research conference, growing from 50 participants to over 500 student researchers annually. We've fostered countless research collaborations and launched many academic careers.

What is SOAR?

The Student Organization for Academic Research (SOAR) is an annual conference that brings together the brightest student minds to share their research and build the future of academia. Think of it as the Avengers of student research conferences!

Research Presentations

Students present their cutting-edge research through oral presentations and poster sessions

Academic Excellence

Promoting high-quality research across all disciplines

Community Building

Creating lasting connections between student researchers

Frequently Asked Questions

Who can attend SOAR?

All undergraduate and graduate students are welcome to attend and present their research.

What types of research are accepted?

We accept research from all disciplines - STEM, humanities, social sciences, and interdisciplinary work.

Is there a registration fee?

Registration is free for all students thanks to our generous sponsors!

How do I submit my abstract?

Abstract submissions open in January 2026. Details will be posted on our website.
